                    <p>Brought to you by the festival team and local traders, some very special performers from our
                        Sound Tracks concert and others come to the Triangle.</p>

                    <p>Can’t leave the Triangle? Follow the trail for a magical afternoon of music and poetry in some of our best-loved shops:</p>

                    <h2 class="listing">Vintage hub, Church Road and St Aubyn’s Road cul de sac</h2>

                    <p><strong>12:00</strong> <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/CrystalPalaceCommunityChoir/">Crystal Palace Community Choir</a><br>
                    A home-grown choir that welcomes all and sings everything!</p>

                    <h2 class="listing">Crystal Palace Antiques, Jasper Road</h2>

                    <p><strong>12:15</strong> Favourite and new performers from Beyond Words<br>
                    Your local regular literary and musical spinners of magic present Matthew Caley and Orlanda Marsden</p>

                    <p><strong>13:00</strong> <a href="http://www.worldofsurprises.co.uk/">Brother G and The Trouble</a><br>
                    Experimental music and sound with spoken word using piano, reel to reel tape machines, accordion, clarinet, percussion and the voice.</p>

                    <h2 class="listing">Kaleidoscope fine art and craft fair, Haynes Lane</h2>

                    <p><strong>13:30</strong> <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/CrystalPalaceCommunityChoir/">Crystal Palace Community Choir</a><br>
                    A home-grown choir that welcomes all and sings everything!</p>

                    <h2 class="listing">Blue Door Bicycles, Central Hill</h2>

                    <p><strong>14:00</strong> Tim Bridgen – vibraphone<br>
                    Percussionist Tim will transport listeners to the vibe of a late night jazz club, playing an eclectic mix of music from J.S Bach to Joe Locke</p>

                    <p><strong>14:45</strong> Favourite and new performers from Beyond Words<br>
                    – Your local regular literary and musical spinners of magic present Joe Cullen and Rosanna Raymond</p>

                    <h2 class="listing">The Secret Garden, Coxwell Road</h2>

                    <p><strong>14:45</strong> <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/CrystalPalaceCommunityChoir/">Crystal Palace Community Choir</a><br>
                    A home-grown choir that welcomes all and sings everything!</p>

                    <p><strong>15:30</strong> <a href="http://www.keziah.co.uk/">Keziah Thomas</a> – harp<br>
                    Award-winning local harpist presents music first performed at the Crystal Palace by John Thomas and Arthur Sullivan</p>

                    <p><strong>16:15</strong> Abigail Sudbury – soprano<br>
                    Continuing the theme of music at the Crystal Palace, songs by Arthur Sullivan, Ivor Novello and August Manns accompanied by the harp</p>

                    <p><strong>17:00</strong> Favourite and new performers from Beyond Words<br>
                        Your local regular literary and musical spinners of magic present Mars Willis - story-teller and musician and Sophie Herxheimer – poet and artist.</p>

